name: Honeycomb Effect
description:
We are all connected

Like the cells in a honeycomb, 
we each have our own unique cell that makes us, us.
This simulation we call life, is a web of connections, 
an ever evolving matrix, a honeycomb of our own, 
just as unique as our respective units.
As time passes, the individual cells encircling you start to grow and change.
The universe connects all of us for a reason, 
as we bridge with others, 
their cells become closer in proximity to your cell. 
Without over complicating this elementary ideology, 
Here and Now - our cells have never been more connected.

Welcome to the honeycomb


matrix
noun
1.an environment or material in which something develops; 
a surrounding medium or structure.
